First you need to take the @flank steak{4} out of your fridge to bring it up to room temperature. Preheat your #oven{} to 220 degrees and boil a #kettle{} of @water{300%ml} for later. Chop the @new potatoes{2} into small 2cm cubes (no need to peel). Lightly crush the @black peppercorns{1.5%tsp} in a #pestle and mortar{}.

> If you don't have a pestle and mortar, put them between two sheets of tinfoil/clingfilm and give them a little whack with a rolling pin.

Remove the @rosemary{1} leaves from their stalks and chop very finely. Put your potatoes on a #baking tray{}, sprinkle on your rosemary leaves and drizzle over some @olive oil{}. Add a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{}. Give the baking tray a good shake so your potatoes are evenly coated and cook on the top shelf of your oven, for ~{30%minutes} until crispy (give the #baking tray{} another shake halfway through cooking).

Peel and very finely chop the @echalion shallot{1} and chop the @broccoli{2} into florets.

Put your broccoli florets on another baking tray, add a splash of @olive oil{}, a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{} and pop in your oven on the middle shelf for ~{10%minutes} until slightly crispy.

Once your steak is at room temperature, season with a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Heat a large #frying pan{} on high heat with a splash of @oil{}. When almost smoking, lay your steak in the pan and press it down.

> Lay the steak away from your body to stop oil spitting at you.

Cook for ~{3%minutes} on each side if you like it medium. Only turn your steak once and rest on a warm #plate{} when cooked.

> Cook for a little longer if you like your steak well done.

Once your steak is removed from the pan, turn the heat to medium-low and add another small drizzle of @olive oil{} along with your shallot. Cook for ~{2%minutes} then add your peppercorns. After another ~{1%minute}, add your boiled water and stir in the @beef stock pot{1}.

Bubble away for a few minutes until your sauce has reduced by half, take off the heat and stir in the @crème fraîche{1}, this is your peppercorn sauce.

> For a decadent touch, add a small knob of butter at this point (if you have some). Slice your steak diagonally into 1cm strips.

Serve your steak with a drizzle of peppercorn sauce and your roasted potatoes and broccoli on the side.